%page
12
Variants as set constraints


Variants can be seen as sets of possible values:

	[tag1 ... tagn] = {tag1,...,tagn}


Polymorphic variants introduce constraints

	α[> tag1 ... tagn] ⇔ α ⊃ {tag1,...,tagn}
	α[< tag1 ... tagn] ⇔ α ⊂ {tag1,...,tagn}

